      <hedline>
        <hl1>Melting-Pot Politics</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Edward Spychalsky Jr letter, replying to Oct 11 editorial, says Rep Rick A Lazio and Gov George E Pataki are not questioning Hillary Rodham Clinton's right to become a New Yorker, only her qualifications to represent a state she is new to in Senate</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Defining a New Yorker'' (editorial, Oct. 11):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Defining a New Yorker'' (editorial, Oct. 11):</p>
        <p>I think it is unfair to criticize Rick A. Lazio and Gov. George E. Pataki as challenging Hillary Rodham Clinton's right to ''jump into'' the melting pot that is, in their opinion, New York.</p>
        <p>Throughout the campaign, I have yet to hear either man challenge Mrs. Clinton's decision to take up residence and become a part of New York. What I have heard is their reluctance to grant such a newcomer, still unschooled in the ways of New York, the opportunity to lead the state.</p>
        <p>EDWARD SPYCHALSKY JR.  Amityville, N.Y., Oct. 11, 2000</p>
      </block>
